            "captcha":{
                "header":"NEED SOME SLEEP?",
                "message":"Enter the characters in the box below",
                "ok":"OK"
            },
            "cityplannermoveavailable":{
                "header":"New Feature!",
                "message":"With the City Planner built, we can now move buildings even when they're under construction or repair!"
            },
            "didyouknow":{
                "buttonlabel":"Awesome!",
                "header":"Did you know?..",
                "message1":"Have a lot of friends. You'll get more resources, your jobs will finish faster, and your defenses will be much stronger.",
                "message10":"Stockpiles are your next important buildings to protect. Resource producers come next.",
                "message11":"Keep your Pigeon Post notifications on. This way you'll get to know if something requires your attention.",
                "message12":"Do not engage Bombard Tower or Flamer Tower with masses of mercs. Since they deal area damage, you may lose your army instantly.",
                "message13":"Make sure you have a decent empty stock capacity before an attack. You can never guess the loot you'll acquire from an attack. Don't let it go wasted.",
                "message14":"Quest rewards are added to your stores even if your stock capacity is full. So relax, and finish them anytime you desire.",
                "message15":"If you want to level up quickly, try to go PvP. Player vs. Player battles give you more XP than early Clan cities.",
                "message16":"If you think that you can't beat someone with only 1 attack, plan accordingly. It might be a good idea to go for the towers in the first attack. Then when you clear up the path, you can go with the looters to maximize your gains.",
                "message17":"Try to get as much workers as possible quickly. This will greatly increase your construction abilities.",
                "message18":"Use your walls to lure the enemy, not to block it. Try to create mazes that will create a long path for attackers where you will have time for your towers to finish them off. Just like a tower defense!",
                "message19":"Make sure you collect Gold from your City Center regulary. You can do just about anything with this precious currency!",
                "message2":"Go Facebook Post hunting regularly. Posts of your friends will yield a significant amount of resources and parts for your arsenal.",
                "message20":"Alliances are a great way to enhance your gameplay experience. You can attack enemies of your alliance friends, send them mercs to use in combats and race for alliance ranking!",
                "message21":"Try laddering up in leagues if you like PvP experience. Leagues give you massive Iron Production bonus continuously and top 3 rewards at season endings.",
                "message22":"Follow events for massive loot and exclusive prices. New mercs, catapults and many other support items can be unlocked in Event store to give you the ultimate edge!",
                "message23":"Did you know that Bearwolf becomes a looter at level 6?",
                "message24":"Did you know that Mightosour’s favourite target becomes Defensive Buildings at level 6?",
                "message25":"Send mercs to your alliance members regularly. Help them in their combats. One for all, all for one!",
                "message26":"Smart attack can get you many easy opponents that you can loot. But remember: You can only attack them once!",
                "message27":"Special Offers are a great way of getting cheap gold. Do not miss them to have the upper edge!",
                "message28":"The BP you gain in PvP combats depends on the BP difference between you and your opponent. The more you have, the more you lose if you’re defeated. The less you have, the more you gain if you are victorious.",
                "message29":"Did you know that the Alliance Points you have contributed are subtracted from that alliance, when you leave it? When you get in again, those points are remembered and added to total alliance points.",
                "message3":"Attack Clans while you have a decent spent iron/loot gain percentage. In general a ratio < 1 is considered good.",
                "message30":"Looters are a great way to enhance the resources you get from a city. They loot up to 5 times more resources than the regular Mercenaries!",
                "message31":"Beasts are the real game changer. Upgrade City Center to Level 4 and get one these powerful units!",
                "message32":"Beasts are effective both in your attacks & defenses. Try to find the suitable one for your strategies by trying each of them.",
                "message33":"You can extend the combat time by 1 minute, 15 seconds prior to the combat end. This can be the difference between victory and defeat. Use it wisely!",
                "message34":"You can’t re-join an alliance for 1 month if you’re kicked or you’ve left it.",
                "message35":"Fire traps damage both air and ground units while buried spikes only affect ground targets.",
                "message36":"Fire traps only get triggered by Beasts, Hezarfen, Rock’n Gaul, Pharaoh Warrior, Mongolian Gargantuan and Gentle Healer.",
                "message37":"You can re-arm all triggered traps by clicking on one of them and select desired re-arm option.",
                "message38":"A single job in your city can only be helped 14 times at max. This will approximately finish 50% of that process.",
                "message39":"If you lack in finding enemies, join a crowded alliance and look for alliance enemies.",
                "message4":"Deploy high HP mercs first to get attention of towers. They will soak a lot of damage while your hard hitting mercs get the job done.",
                "message5":"Following quests is the easiest way for fast progress since the rewards are really high.",
                "message6":"Do not attack higher level players. In general, a player should be 1-2 level lower than you for a succesful and productive attack.",
                "message7":"Try to find attack targets that have already damaged towers from previous attacks. Let others do the hard thing, go get the easy loot.",
                "message8":"Do not overcommit and deploy more mercs than you need. Even if your mercs survive the battle, they won't return back to your city at the end of the combat!",
                "message9":"Most important target you have to defend is your City Center. You lose a significant amount of resources if it falls."
            },
